data.title: Men At Work - Down Under vs Toto - Africa
data.meta_description: Both of these are unofficial anthems for their respective continents. Which song do you guys think is better and why?
data.text:
House Lannister

6x Platinum Member

Would be Twitcher/YouTuber

Joined: May 2015

Posts: 6,522

Post by House Lannister on

There's more subtlety to the goofiness of Africa which makes it a staple at Desert Bus and caused Weezer to cover it about 25 years later.

It's missing from Down Under which means it's forgotten about unless we're covering early 1980s massive hits.

Post by Deleted on

Down Under easily.Africa has to be one of the worst songs of the 80's . don't know why Weezer had to bring it back.

that's quite the hot take but i wish that opinion burned you back :)

Post by Golden Bluebird on

"Africa". Never really liked "Down Under" all that much. It's good, but not great.

Also, it's worth mentioning that both of these songs were #1 songs back to back, so you can add this to the Funny Chart Coincidences if someone hasn't.
